channel.title: Two Things
channel.description:
[center][u][b]Ok, I Got Two Questions[/b][/u][/center]
[ul][li]How Do you make your commands show up on the menu page or on ::commands? [/li] [li]How do you make when they train it give more exp than what it's giving?[/li][/ul]

item.title: Two Things
item.dc:creator: @hallowed_soul hallowed soul
item.description:
@hallowed_soul wrote:

Find Another Command, Like ::help Or ::info That Brings Up A menu And Search It As "help or "info Then Change To Commands, And Modify The Text To Commands You Want

Read full topic

Either there isn’t a command, or it’s command.equalsIgnoreCase(“commands”)

item.title: Two Things
item.dc:creator: @hallowed_soul hallowed soul
item.description:
@hallowed_soul wrote:

To Make It Give More Xp, Find The ID Of The Object You Train On And Search It, As Case (ID) Then Scroll A TINY Bit, And You Will See Soemthing Relating To Xp, Change That To Whatever You Desire

Read full topic

item.title: Two Things
item.dc:creator: @Waffles1 Waffles!!
item.description:
@Waffles1 wrote:

::commands
Search ‘command.startsWith(“commands”)’ in your client.java. Everything that shows up on that list is under that.

XP rate
Search the case ID in the client.java. The ID of the case is the ID of the object.

Read full topic
